cs.MS, cs.SY, q-bio.QM, q-bio.TO, q-bio.SC 

Reasoning: 
- cs.MS (Mathematical Software): The paper proposes a new surface language for the modelling of biological systems behaviour, which can be compiled into a standard CWC model. This involves mathematical and computational aspects, making cs.MS a likely category. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper discusses the modelling and simulation of biological systems behaviour, which can be seen as a control problem. 
- q-bio.QM (Quantitative Methods): The paper proposes a modelling language for the representation of biological systems behaviour, which involves quantitative methods. 
- q-bio.TO (Tissues and Organs): The paper discusses the modelling of spatial interactions in biological systems, which is relevant to the study of tissues and organs. 
- q-bio.SC (Subcellular Processes): The paper discusses the modelling of compartments in biological systems, which is relevant to the study of subcellular processes.
